cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.NA. 

The paper deals with the problem of recovering low-rank and bisparse matrices from one-bit measurements, which is a problem in compressed sensing. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves theoretical analysis and optimization, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper uses concepts from numerical analysis and linear algebra, which could place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
